Comment: F.B.Hagedorn and J.B.Marion Phys.Rev. 108 (1957) 1015;
     Excitation functions at nine angles (15, 25, 40, 60, 75,  90, 
105, 120, 140 deg lab) for the reaction 15N(p,a0)12C are  reported 
for incident proton energies from 0.9 to 1.3 MeV. At a  laboratory 
angle of 140 deg the excitation function has been extended to  2.9 
MeV. 
     Electrostatic  accelerator  was  used.  The  15N  target  was 
prepared in an electromagnetic isotope separator by  bombarding  a 
beryllium foil with 20-keV 15N ions. This foil had  an  equivalent 
thickness of 25 keV for 1 MeV  protons,  and  ~3*10^17  atoms/cm^2 
were deposited in its  surface.  A  180-degree  double-focussing 
magnetic spectrometer was used to detect particles.
     Graphical data are only presented.
